<paragraph id="7F05A58E4D65DEF3FF26AD6798FEF1E7" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<bibRefCitation id="90F01A62FCA5C76D255372A7AEE4F16C" author="Hartmann-Schroeder, G" journalOrPublisher="Helgolander Meeresuntersuchungen" pageId="9" pageNumber="98" pagination="389 - 403" title="Zur Polychaetenfauna in rezenten hydrothermalen Komplexmassivsulfiderzen (&quot; Schwarze Raucher &quot;) am Ostpazifischen Rucken bei 21 ° 30 ' S." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02367206" volume="46" year="1992">
<normalizedToken id="FD91F32D03E2ABF086A45C3DE2A20895" originalValue="Hartmann-Schröder’s">Hartmann-Schroeder's</normalizedToken>
(1992)
</bibRefCitation>
diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="4462465B175ED74A3203BE2817634EB4" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Thermiphione" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thermiphione" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Thermiphione</taxonomicName>
has been amended to accommodate the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName id="B8336B9AFDB93F3B4A4985AEE744E601" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Iphionella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iphionella risensis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="risensis">Iphionella risensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B65888E561408148E6DACF7E8978735A" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Thermiphione" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thermiphione rapanui" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="rapanui">Thermiphione rapanui</taxonomicName>
sp. n. The genus now comprises 
<taxonomicName id="A50DA5B9BE144404A3D1DEA631186ADC" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Thermiphione" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thermiphione fijiensis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fijiensis">Thermiphione fijiensis</taxonomicName>
(Figure 5A, D), 
<taxonomicName id="A23943931321649FE7DD51B2DBE21B49" genus="T." lsidName="T. risensis" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="species" species="risensis">T. risensis</taxonomicName>
(Figure 5B, E), 
<taxonomicName id="AD4BD8B22960CF7CFA2DF6DDD7E28418" genus="T." lsidName="T. tufari" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="species" species="tufari">T. tufari</taxonomicName>
(Figure 5C), and 
<taxonomicName id="2496E6F9032128293397AE73956F42C1" genus="T." lsidName="T. rapanui" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="species" species="rapanui">T. rapanui</taxonomicName>
sp. n (Figs 6-9). The morphology of these taxa and phylogenetic evidence suggests that segment and elytral numbers are more variable than in the previous diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName id="29C2A20D0FB03FB7655B0EEFF3F428FF" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Thermiphione" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thermiphione" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Thermiphione</taxonomicName>
all have smooth palps, but this is plesiomorphic for 
<taxonomicName id="87C606EF03687722DDB3B210CE2E9930" family="Iphionidae" lsidName="" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="family">Iphionidae</taxonomicName>
. The absence of eyes may be an apomorphic state, depending on the eventual placement of 
<taxonomicName id="E2D0DF5B8A51311DF0FC6059843D6102" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Iphionella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iphionella philippinensis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="philippinensis">Iphionella philippinensis</taxonomicName>
, which was not included here owing to the lack of material for DNA sequencing. Similarly, the loss of lateral antennae may also be an apomorphy for 
<taxonomicName id="039D3B7F7E5A9DC82D1FCBAB1F64D08C" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Thermiphione" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thermiphione" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Thermiphione</taxonomicName>
once the position of 
<taxonomicName id="0EB234C7D32B7C350D5974E64A24B465" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Iphionella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iphionella philippinensis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="philippinensis">Iphionella philippinensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="72A2BFB794CA8D8E45D810107F4E6BA4" class="Polychaeta" family="Iphionidae" genus="Iphionides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iphionides glabra" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="glabra">Iphionides glabra</taxonomicName>
, which also lack them, is resolved.
</paragraph>
